I200405290105 (3.0RC1)

If an exception occurs in an inner class the stack-trace may be printed to the
console. In 3.0M7 you could click on a message like 

"java.lang.NullPointerException
	at Test$1.doIt(Test.java:9)"

and the editor would be positioned to line 9 in Test.java.

In 3.0RC1 this does no longer work.

Example: 

public class Test {
    interface IFoo {
        void doIt();
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        IFoo foo = new IFoo() {
            public void doIt() {
                String s = null;
                int i = s.length();
            }
        };
        foo.doIt();
    }
}

In 3.0M7 you can click on "at Test$1.doIt(Test.java:10)" and the editor gets
positioned correctly.

in 3.0RC1 you only get a dialog telling you that "Source not found for Test$1".
